            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">A short prayer of protection, widely circulated. Commonly
                     known also as al-Dawr al-aʿlā or Dawr al-aʿlā. OY lists nine separate
                     commentaries, which appear to have been written in 12–13th centuries.</note>
               <note type="structure"/>
               <note type="contentsNote"/>
            </noteGrp>
            <!-- Stemmatics -->
            <note type="stemmatics">There are many mss., all attributed to IA, though none can be
                  considered historic. The earliest dated copy is 994H. Suha Taji-Farouki, who has
                  produced the critical edition, (see below) is convinced of its authenticity on the
                  basis of textual analyis, and chains of transmission on various mss. Published as
                  Prayer for Spiritual Elevation and Protection (Oxford 2006).</note>
